## Summary

The skill sync check in `session-start.sh` previously used timestamp comparison (`-nt`) to detect divergence between `templates/commands/` and `.claude/commands/`. This produced false positives after `git checkout` or `cp` operations that updated mtimes without changing content.

Upgraded to `md5sum` content comparison — only warns when files actually differ.

## Prerequisites

- `.claude/hooks/session-start.sh` must contain the `## Step 8b. Skill sync check` section

## Change

In `.claude/hooks/session-start.sh`, replace the sync check loop body:

**Before:**
```bash
if [[ ! -f "$dst" ]] || [[ "$src" -nt "$dst" ]]; then
  SYNC_OUT_OF_SYNC="$SYNC_OUT_OF_SYNC $fname"
fi
```

**After:**
```bash
if [[ ! -f "$dst" ]]; then
  SYNC_OUT_OF_SYNC="$SYNC_OUT_OF_SYNC $fname"
else
  src_md5=$(md5sum "$src" | cut -d' ' -f1)
  dst_md5=$(md5sum "$dst" | cut -d' ' -f1)
  [[ "$src_md5" != "$dst_md5" ]] && SYNC_OUT_OF_SYNC="$SYNC_OUT_OF_SYNC $fname"
fi
```

## Batch Sequence

No dependencies. Apply independently.

## Verification

Run: `bash -n .claude/hooks/session-start.sh` — should produce no errors.
